# 🛡️ BODIUM TOYS – Security Audit Report

Welcome to the Security Audit Report homepage for Botium Toys. This section of the cybersecurity portfolio documents the current state of technical controls, compliance readiness, and strategic recommendations following a detailed risk assessment.

---

## 🧭 Purpose

This report outlines the findings from a simulated security assessment conducted as part of the Google Cybersecurity Certificate program. The goal is to demonstrate practical application of industry-aligned frameworks and recommend improvements to strengthen Botium Toys’ security posture.

---

## 📄 Contents

- [Assessment Summary](BODIUM Assessment Recommendations)  
  A high-level overview of findings, recommendations, and justifications for proposed control enhancements.

- [Controls & Compliance Checklist](./Botium_Security_Checklist.md)  
  A structured, actionable list of technical controls and regulatory best practices including PCI DSS, GDPR, and SOC 1/2.

- [Supporting Documentation](#) *(Add links to additional artifacts as needed)*  
  - Network diagrams  
  - Control categories reference  
  - Incident response templates  
  - Risk assessment report  

---

## 🧠 Key Areas Evaluated

- Principle of Least Privilege  
- Intrusion Detection System (IDS)  
- Password Management & Encryption  
- Disaster Recovery Planning  
- GDPR, PCI DSS, SOC 1 & 2 Alignment  
- Monitoring Legacy Systems  

